#. <section class="sutta" id="sn3.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. Shackles"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Bandhanasutta"
msgstr "10. Shackles"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.10:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena raññā pasenadinā kosalena mahājanakāyo bandhāpito "
"hoti, appekacce rajjūhi appekacce andūhi appekacce saṅkhalikāhi."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a large group of people had been put in shackles by King "
"Pasenadi of Kosala—some in ropes, some in manacles, some in chains."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.77"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.175"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.10:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then several mendicants robed up in the morning and, taking their bowls and "
"robes, entered Sāvatthī for alms."

msgctxt "sn3.10:2.2"
msgid ""
"Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after the meal, when they returned from alms-round, they went up to "
"the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what was happening."

msgctxt "sn3.10:2.3"
msgid ""
"“idha, bhante, raññā pasenadinā kosalena mahājanakāyo bandhāpito, appekacce "
"rajjūhi appekacce andūhi appekacce saṅkhalikāhī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.10:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha recited these "
"verses:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.10:4.1"
msgid "“Na taṃ daḷhaṃ bandhanamāhu dhīrā,"
msgstr "“The wise say that shackle is not strong"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:4.2"
msgid "Yadāyasaṃ dārujaṃ pabbajañca;"
msgstr "that’s made of iron, wood, or knots."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:4.3"
msgid "Sārattarattā maṇikuṇḍalesu,"
msgstr "But infatuation with jewels and earrings,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:4.4"
msgid "Puttesu dāresu ca yā apekkhā."
msgstr "concern for your partners and children:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.176"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.1"
msgid "Etaṃ daḷhaṃ bandhanamāhu dhīrā,"
msgstr "this the wise say is a strong shackle"

# I assume asithila, with a elided metri causa. BB’s “supple” notwithstanding, sithila yields exactly the wrong meaning.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.2"
msgid "Ohārinaṃ sithilaṃ duppamuñcaṃ;"
msgstr "that drags you down, tight, hard to escape."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.3"
msgid "Etampi chetvāna paribbajanti,"
msgstr "They cut this too and go forth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.4"
msgid "Anapekkhino kāmasukhaṃ pahāyā”ti."
msgstr "with no worries, having given up sensual pleasures.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.5"
msgid "Paṭhamo vaggo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.10:6.1"
msgid "Daharo puriso jarā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:6.2"
msgid "piyaṃ attānarakkhito;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:6.3"
msgid "Appakā aḍḍakaraṇaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:6.4"
msgid "mallikā yaññabandhananti."
msgstr ""
